// Explicit `return` must seal the basic block with Terminator::Return so
// codegen actually returns at that program point. Codegen emits the
// function return from the block terminator, not the MirStatement::Return
// THIR marker — without sealing, post-return source code keeps executing
// and the user-visible behaviour is a no-op `return`.
//
// This fixture exits 7 from the early-return path. If the early return
// did NOT seal its block, the subsequent `exit(99)` would still run and
// the process would exit 99. Observing exit code 7 proves the early
// return actually terminates the function at that point.
fn main() -> i64 {
    return 7;
    exit(99)
}
